article.description: Maizen Fausett had 13 points and 10 rebounds to lead Southern Utah to a 59-53 win over Montana State on Saturday.
article.headline: Fausett lifts S. Utah past Montana St. 59-53
article.linkText: Fausett lifts S. Utah past Montana St. 59-53
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Maizen Fausett had 13 points and 10 rebounds to lead Southern Utah to a 59-53 win over Montana State on Saturday. Harrison Butler had 12 points and eight rebounds for Southern Utah (9-5, 2-1 Big Sky Conference). John Knight III added 12 points. Cameron Oluyitan had 6 points despite coming into the matchup as the Thunderbirds' second leading scorer at 13 points per game. He was 0 of 4 from 3-point range. Neither team was able to get much going offensively in the first 20 minutes. Southern Utah trailed 21-17 heading to the locker room at the half, but the Thunderbirds came back in the second half to earn the victory. Both teams set season lows for scoring in the first half. The Thunderbirds' 17 first-half points were the lowest of the season for the hosts, while the 21 first-half points for the Bobcats marked the fewest of the season for the visitors. Harald Frey had 14 points for the Bobcats (8-7, 2-2). Amin Adamu added 12 points and nine rebounds. Ladan Ricketts had 10 points. Southern Utah faces Idaho State on the road on Thursday. Montana State takes on Idaho on the road on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
